example.p:
The system of equations

        \begin{array}{rl}
        2x+3y-z \amp = 2\\
        -x+y+z \amp =4\\
        3x-y-z \amp = 3
        \end{array}

        corresponds to the augmented matrix

        \begin{bmatrix}
        2 \amp 3 \amp -1 \amp 2\\
        -1 \amp 1 \amp 1 \amp 4\\
        3 \amp -1 \amp -1 \amp 3
        \end{bmatrix}

        Now we multiply row 2 by \lambda=-3 (R_2\gets -3R_2) to get
        the matrix

        \begin{bmatrix}
        2 \amp 3 \amp -1 \amp 2\\
        3 \amp -3 \amp -3 \amp -12\\
        3 \amp -1 \amp -1 \amp 3
        \end{bmatrix}

        which corresponds to the system of equations

        \begin{array}{rl}
        2x+3y-z \amp = 2\\
        3x-3y-3z \amp =-12\\
        3x-y-z \amp = 3
        \end{array}

Eliminating x from the second equation:
\begin{array}{rl} -x+y+z \amp =4\\ 2x+3y-z \amp = 2\\ 3x-y-z \amp = 3 \end{array}
corresponds to the augmented matrix
\begin{bmatrix} -1 \amp 1 \amp 1 \amp 4\\ 2 \amp 3 \amp -1 \amp 2\\ 3 \amp -1 \amp -1 \amp 3 \end{bmatrix}
Now we replace row 2 by the sum of row 2 and twice row 1 (R_2\gets R_2+2R_1) to get the matrix
\begin{bmatrix} -1 \amp 1 \amp 1 \amp 4\\ 0 \amp 5 \amp 1 \amp 10\\ 3 \amp -1 \amp -1 \amp 3 \end{bmatrix}
which corresponds to the system of linear equations
\begin{array}{rl} - x+y+z \amp =4\\ 5y+z \amp =10\\ 3x-y-z \amp = 3 \end{array}

